<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-25"><hi rend="italic">March 25,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Minister for foreign affairs said he was not in condition to speak of
                            affairs of the department of which he had been in charge only one day;
                                <pb facs="0446" n="1180" xml:id="pg_1180"/> but he promised to
                            consider <hi rend="italic">Alliança</hi> incident before everything,
                            assuring me of his desire and hope that it will receive solution equal
                            to his interest to maintain reciprocal friendship and consideration
                            existing between the two nations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>